Uruk <a href="javascript:card_browser(303)">Armor</a>y x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(36)">Spies of Saruman</a> x2<br>
Savagery to Match Their Numbers x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(56)">Uruk-hai Sword</a> x3<br>
<br>
Adventure Path:<br>
<br>
Prancing Pony<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(214)">Trollshaw Forest</a><br>
Rivendell Courtyard<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(226)">Moria Stairway</a><br>
Bridge of Khazud-Dum<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(230)">Dimrill Dale</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(233)">Anduin Wilderland</a>s or <br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(237)">Pillars of the Kings</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(241)">Slopes of Amon Hen</a><br>
  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Strategy:<br>
<br>
Don&#8217;t bid anything&#8212;don&#8217;t help out those burden, corruption, Enduring Evil decks.  I&#8217;ve got three copies of Aragorn which means he&#8217;s coming out at some point.  Extra copies can heal him because a healthy Aragorn is a happy Aragorn.  Used King in Exile because he&#8217;s a great card for this deck.  He can heal Arwen and Boromir.  Multiples of possessions to get  them out fast, discarding the extra weapons will help with through put which will help with card advantage by putting the cards I need in my hand.  Last Alliance to boost Aragorn and Boromir, Arwen&#8217;s Fate in case she needs it (can always discard if things are rolling), The Choice of Luthien to give Aragorn a break, Northern Kingdoms to boost everybody, Versatility (along with Greenleaf and Aragorn&#8217;s Bow) to get rid of those Nasties lurking at rivers and forests.  Tale of Gil-Galad and Saga of Elendil to give Aragorn and Legolas an extra vitality to play with.  Multiples of No Stranger to the Shadows means someone basically moves for free.  Athelas to get rid of conditions and heal.  Armor to deal with Uruks, damage +1, etc.<br>
<br>
Shadow side is standard beat down.  Expensive minions but each able to win a skirmish or at least make opponent burn cards.  Troop means no weapons, Guards ensure the strongest Companion won&#8217;t block him,  The Armories and Spies of Saruman to deal with archery and especially direct damage.  Savagery to Match Their Numbers to boost an Uruk, Swords until I can get more Savagery, Saruman&#8217;s Ambitions are free, don&#8217;t have to spot to play, so they don&#8217;t clog my hand, and they can turn a skirmish in an Uruk&#8217;s favor real fast.<br>
 </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=20430"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=20430" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
